President Biden visited the Lockheed Martin Pike County Operations facility in Troy, Alabama to express his gratitude to the workers for their contribution to supporting Ukraine's fight for freedom. He commended the bravery of the Ukrainian fighters and highlighted the atrocities committed by Russian forces. Biden emphasized the importance of the United States and its allies providing weapons and support to Ukraine to defend against Russian aggression. He mentioned the significance of the Javelin missiles manufactured at the facility and their effectiveness in combating armored targets. Biden urged Congress to pass funding to continue sending weapons to Ukraine and replenishing the United States' own stock. He also stressed the need for the United States to invest in research and development to maintain its technological advantage and manufacturing capabilities. The President concluded his speech by expressing his gratitude and appreciation for the workers' efforts.